The paper combines multiple fields such as secure multi-party computation, mechanism design, deep learning, and control theory to achieve a decentralised stablecoin with provable security and complex monetary policies. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories such as cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
